20gurus%2C%20everything%20felt%20like%20an%20ongoing%20tug%20of%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20joined%20numerous%20parenting%20groups%20on%20social%20media%20to%20get%20a%20better%20idea%20of%20how%20to%20handle%20certain%20situations%2C%20such%20as%20my%20son's%20refusal%20to%20brush%20his%20teeth.%20Instead%20of%20seeing%20rational%20responses%2C%20I%20was%20shocked%20to%20find%20some%20parents%20suggesting%20to%20avoid%20brushing%20teeth%20to%20keep%20children%20happy%20while%20defining%20it%20as%20%26quot%3Bnegotiable%26quot%3B%20This%20seemed%20unacceptable%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222a760c63-5753-4e97-8968-18ef46819204%5C%22%3EI%20needed%20to%20change%20my%20parenting%20strategy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20quickly%20realized%20that%20every%20child%20has%20varying%20levels%20of%20noncompliance%2C%20and%20in%20order%20for%20%3Cem%3Emy%3C%2Fem%3E%20son%20to%20assimilate%20well%20outside%20the%20home%2C%20he%20couldn't%20keep%20up%20with%20his%20behavior%20(which%20I%20had%20admittedly%20enabled).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20could%20no%20longer%20align%20myself%20with%20the%20parental%20restrictiveness%20of%20the%20movement.%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20treading%20on%20eggshells%20all%20the%20time.%20The%20pressure%20to%20be%20the%20perfect%2C%20patient%20parent%20was%20wearing%20me%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20found%20gentle%20parenting%20to%20be%20unrealistic%20and%20stressful%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20making%20me%20miserable.%20A%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fgentle-parenting-can-be-really-hard-on-parents-new-research-suggests-217508%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20small%20but%20recent%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%2040%25%20of%20gentle%20parents%20who%20were%20interviewed%20confessed%20to%20being%20overwhelmed%2C%20exhausted%2C%20hard%20on%20themselves%2C%20and%20uncertain.%20I%20can%20definitely%20relate.%20Confining%20myself%20to%20a%20parenting%20style%20wasn't%20feasible%20%E2%80%94%20I%20needed%20to%20be%20adaptable%20to%20changing%20situations%20and%20moods%20with%20my%20son%2C%20which%20required%20a%20blended%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20I%20came%20to%20the%20conclusion%20that%20gentle%20parenting%20is%20way%20too%20gentle.%20Children%20need%20to%20learn%20that%20the%20world%20doesn't%20revolve%20around%20their%20personal%20feelings.%20Children%20need%20a%20level%20of%20firmness%20and%20accountability.%20There%20should%20be%20balance%20instead%20of%20leaning%20toward%20extremes%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20fitting%20into%20parenting%20structures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20all%20honesty%2C%20drifting%20away%20from%20gentle%20parenting%20made%20me%20realize%20that%20parenting%20is%20more%20about%20trusting%20your%20gut%20than%20following%20scripts%20and%20best%20practices.%20I've%20learned%20to%20be%20myself%20and%20foster%20a%20healthy%20mother-son%20relationship%20with%20my%20child%20by%20enforcing%20firm%20limits%20and%20expectations%20while%20always%20giving%20warmth%20and%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20to%20say%20I%20don't%20believe%20in%20gentle%20parenting.%20I%20definitely%20still%20believe%20in%20treating%20children%20with%20respect%2C%20modeling%20behaviors%20for%20children%2C%20and%20regulating%20myself%20as%20a%20parent%20before%20reacting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-parent-who-ditched-gentle-parenting-it-doesnt-work-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718707861000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666c51f5e079049018191413%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-parent-who-ditched-gentle-parenting-it-doesnt-work-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20I%20was%20pregnant%20I%20learned%20about%20gentle%20parenting.%20As%20my%20child%20grew%2C%20I%20realized%20it%20wasn't%20working%20and%20that%20I%20needed%20to%20change%20how%20I%20parent