olitics.ox.ac.uk%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2024-06%2FDNR%25202024%2520Final%2520lo-res-compressed.pdf%5C%22%3Esurvey%20by%20the%20prestigious%20Reuters%20Institute%20at%20Oxford%20University%3C%2Fa%3E.%20For%20the%20fourth%20time%20in%20a%20row%2C%20the%20survey%20has%20found%20that%20NDTV%2024X7%20is%20the%20country's%20most-watched%20news%20channel%20and%20ndtv.com%20the%20country's%20most%20popular%20news%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Reuters%20institute's%20Digital%20News%20Report%202024%2C%20NDTV%20accounts%20for%2033%20per%20cent%20of%20weekly%20use%20across%20the%20television%2C%20radio%20and%20print%20media.%20Likewise%2C%20ndtv.com%2C%20is%20ahead%20of%20the%20competition%20with%2027%20per%20cent%20weekly%20use%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Ffu621ado_reuters-institute-report_625x300_18_June_24.jpg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20the%20methodology%20used%20in%20the%20study%2C%20the%20Reuters%20Institute%20has%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThese%20data%20are%20based%20on%20a%20survey%20of%20mainly%20English-speaking%2C%20online%20news%20users%20in%20India%20-%20a%20small%20subset%20of%20a%20larger%2C%20more%20diverse%2C%20media%20market.%20Findings%20in%20this%20online%20poll%20are%20not%20nationally%20representative%20and%20will%20tend%20to%20under-represent%20the%20continued%20importance%20of%20traditional%20media%20such%20as%20TV%20and%20print.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2F3bdlc8t8_reuters-institute-report_625x300_18_June_24.jpg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20institute%20noted%20that%20its%20survey%20found%20that%20for%20a%20new%20generation%20of%20Indians%2C%20their%20main%20sources%20of%20news%20is%20often%20social%20media%20platforms.%20Almost%20half%20of%20respondents%20use%20YouTube%20(54%25)%20and%20WhatsApp%20(48%25)%20for%20news%20each%20week%2C%20while%20Facebook%20and%20X%20are%20becoming%20less%20popular%2C%20the%20study%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20added%2C%20platforms%20such%20as%20NDTV%20continue%20to%20enjoy%20high%20viewership%20in%20their%20offline%20and%20online%20products%2C%20among%20a%20younger%2C%20urban%2C%20mostly%20English-speaking%20sample.%20%26quot%3BDespite%20a%20general%20decline%20in%C2%A0interest%20in%20news%20over%20the%20years%2C%20print%20(40%25)%20and%20TV%20(46%25)%20remain%20popular%20platforms%20for%20respondents%20to%20access%20news%2C%20especially%20during%20this%20crucial%20election%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20also%20found%20that%20Indian%20readers%20have%20high%20trust%20in%20the%20NDTV%20brand%20as%20a%20source%20for%20news.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20underlined%20that%20partisan%20commercial%20broadcasters%20and%20independent%20digital%20portals%20%26quot%3Bwho%20are%20either%20uncritical%20or%20extremely%20critical%20of%20those%20in%20positions%20of%20power%20are%20actively%20distrusted%20by%20the%20respondents%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20thank%20you%20for%20trusting%20us%20and%20relying%20on%20us%20for%20the%20fastest%20and%20most%20credible%20news%20coverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718699820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F9holpgiao7_ndtv-mics-camera_625x300.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fndtv-tops-reuters-institute-survey-on-india-news-sources-4th-time-in-row-5914759%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Conso